      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While mainstream economic theory often predicts negative outcomes, tariffs are not inherently bad; they are a tool with specific, intended uses. A strong case for tariffs exists when a domestic industry faces predatory dumping from foreign competitors, which is essentially selling goods below cost to destroy local markets. In these targeted situations, tariffs are a necessary defense mechanism to ensure fair competition and prevent economic collapse in vital sectors.",
